column4: var train_score = MAXX(latest_row,companies_history[di_success_prob_training_score])        // latest avg traing scofre
var validation_score = MAXX(latest_row, companies_history[di_success_prob_validation_score])    // latest avg validation
var boost_expo = 0.65 // to get closer to one if good score after the score has been calcualted
var auc_norm  = (MAX((validation_score-0.5),0)) + 0.5  // realize that 0.5 is useless, but boost back up so good is not 0.5
var score  = ((rs_norm + auc_norm)/2) ^ boost_expo  // avg of both normalized score + boosting
var _conf = round(score * 100 ,0) // make it an integer score
_status_",Measure calculating pi scores success prob text. Respects the current filter context.,,a0da8f2c-6910-4440-97a6-77f78705dec5

column4: var applicable_rows_tbl = CALCULATETABLE(users_history, users_history[ci_perf_ramping_status] =""Ramping"" ,  LASTNONBLANK(users_history[_sys_filt_start_date],users_history[_sys_filt_start_date]))  // get only the last entry in each filter context period (e.g. a year)

var active_users_tbl =  filter(applicable_rows_tbl, [trueai_hire_date] <  toDate   && if(isblank([trueai_termination_date]), date(2100,1,1),[trueai_termination_date]) >=  toDate) // make sure we only include reps that are in the active

column1: powerbi\src\Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Automatic Data Enhancement.SemanticModel\definition\tables\metadata_ai_scores.tmdl,Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Automatic Data Enhancement.SemanticModel,metadata_ai_scores,meas.ai_scores_rep_org_calibration,"var latest_table = CALCULATETABLE(TOPN(1,companies_history,companies_history[_sys_processed_as_of],DESC))       // grt the most latest row

column4: var users_match_hr_id = MAXX(latest_table, [users_match_hr_id])         // total matched reps
var users_hr_file = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_hr_file])           // reps in hr file
var users_non_match_hr_id_won_deals = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_non_match_hr_id_won_deals])            // non match won deals reps
var users_non_match_hr_id_pipeline = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_non_match_hr_id_pipeline])          // non match pipeline gen reps
var users_non_match_hr_id_leads = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_non_match_hr_id_leads])          // non match lead gen reps count
var users_match_hr_id_nd_role = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_match_hr_id_nd_role])                  // non match reps with role
var lead_gen_score = (1 - DIVIDE(users_non_match_hr_id_leads, _total_users, 0))               //raw score calculation for each
VAR Row3 = ROW ( ""Value"", pipeline_gen_score, ""Weight"", 1 )          //raw score and weight  added in the table  for each reps count
UNION ( Row1, Row2, Row3, Row4, Row5 )          //creating the table
var _adj_calib = SUMX(temp_tbl, [Value]*[Weight])           // get the adjusted raw score
var _importance = SUMX(temp_tbl, [Weight])                  // sum of the total weight
var raw_score = DIVIDE(_adj_calib, _importance,0)                 // get the score
var boost_expo = 0.9            // we use this to get the closer one value
var score = raw_score^boost_expo     // boosting the actual
res",Measure calculating ai scores rep org calibration. Respects the current filter context.,,7d6d7790-5bbc-4ae0-8506-5f1b9894526e

column4: var  train_score= MAXX(latest_row, companies_history[di_success_prob_training_score])     // get the latest train score
var  validation_score= MAXX(latest_row, companies_history[di_success_prob_validation_score])     // get the latest validation score
var boost_expo = 0.65 // to get closer to one if good score after the score has been calcualted
var validation_score_norm  = (MAX((validation_score-0.5),0)) + 0.5  // realize that 0.5 is useless, but boost back up so good is not 0.5
var score  = ((train_score_norm + validation_score_norm)/2) ^ boost_expo  // avg of both normalized score + boosting
RETURN score",Measure calculating ai scores success factor analysis. Respects the current filter context.,0,c40817e6-7a7d-4281-a04b-007ed3fc01ae

column1: powerbi\src\Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel\definition\tables\metadata_ai_scores.tmdl,Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel,metadata_ai_scores,meas.ai_scores_rep_org_calibration_test,"var latest_table = CALCULATETABLE(TOPN(1,companies_history,companies_history[_sys_processed_as_of],DESC))       // grt the most latest row

column4: var users_match_hr_id = MAXX(latest_table, [users_match_hr_id])         // total matched reps
var users_hr_file = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_hr_file])           // reps in hr file
var users_non_match_hr_id_won_deals = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_non_match_hr_id_won_deals])        // non match won deals reps
var users_non_match_hr_id_pipeline = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_non_match_hr_id_pipeline])          // non match pipeline gen reps
var users_non_match_hr_id_leads = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_non_match_hr_id_leads])          // non match lead gen reps count
var users_match_hr_id_nd_role = MAXX(latest_table, companies_history[users_match_hr_id_nd_role])                  // non match reps with role
var lead_gen_score = (1 - DIVIDE(users_non_match_hr_id_leads, _total_users, 0))               //raw score calculation for each
VAR Row3 = ROW ( ""Value"", pipeline_gen_score, ""Weight"", 1 )          //raw score and weight  added in the table  for each reps count
UNION ( Row1, Row2, Row3, Row4, Row5 )          //creating the table
var _adj_calib = SUMX(temp_tbl, [Value]*[Weight])           // get the adjusted raw score
var _importance = SUMX(temp_tbl, [Weight])                  // sum of the total weight
var raw_score = DIVIDE(_adj_calib, _importance,0)                 // get the score
var boost_expo = 0.9            // we use this to get the closer one value
var score = raw_score^boost_expo     // boosting the actual
matched_reps_score",Measure calculating ai scores rep org calibration test. Respects the current filter context.,0.00%;-0.00%;0.00%,6e7ee0ed-34bf-446a-9ffe-e98ccb212335

column4: var overridden_dates_tbl =  CALCULATETABLE(ssr , cal_end_dates[Date] >=  date(1900,1,1) &&  cal_end_dates[Date] < date(2100,1,1)) -- get current filter context except all dates
// get the tables - break out of filter context (AKK) and override based on first purch and churn

var starting_custs =  Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_start && ssr[trueai_churned_on]  >= period_start)  // client before start of period,  churn after period started
var retained_custs = Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_start && ssr[trueai_churned_on]  >= period_end)  // client before start of period,  churn after period end
var churned_custs = Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_churned_on] >= period_start && ssr[trueai_churned_on] <= period_end)  // churned after period started, before period ended
var ending_custs =  Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_end && ssr[trueai_churned_on]  >= period_end)  // // client before end of period, churn after  period ended
// get the values based on temp tables
var starting_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,starting_custs) // look at last years rev for these

var retained_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,EXCEPT(starting_custs, churned_custs)) // look at last years rev for these

column1: powerbi\src\Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel\definition\tables\performance_metric_1.tmdl,Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel,performance_metric_1,meas.selected_metric_coef,"VAR Txy =

column4: VALUES('users'[col.full_name]),     // Build a table of all reps (one row per user)
NOT ( ISBLANK([x]) || ISBLANK([y]) )  // Exclude rows where either metric is BLANK (zeros are kept)
VAR n      = COUNTROWS(BaseTable)                        // Number of valid reps
VAR AvgX   = AVERAGEX(BaseTable, [x])                    // Average of metric X
VAR AvgY   = AVERAGEX(BaseTable, [y])                    // Average of metric Y
VAR SumXY  = SUMX(BaseTable, ([x] - AvgX) * ([y] - AvgY))// Numerator: covariance
VAR SumX2  = SUMX(BaseTable, POWER([x] - AvgX, 2))       // Denominator part: variance of X
VAR SumY2  = SUMX(BaseTable, POWER([y] - AvgY, 2))       // Denominator part: variance of Y
VAR Denom  = SQRT(SumX2 * SumY2)                         // Denominator = stdev(X) * stdev(Y)

IF( n < 2 || Denom = 0, BLANK(), DIVIDE(SumXY, Denom) ) // Pearson correlation coefficient",Measure calculating selected metric coef. Respects the current filter context.,,c2598b17-0b06-4330-841b-97443bc06242

powerbi\src\Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel\definition\tables\ssr_history.tmdl,Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel,ssr_history,meas.ssr_history_rev_churned_count,"// get the period dates based on current filter contetxt

column4: // this is a test for git
var period_start = [meas.context_date_min]      // get the context max date
var period_end = [meas.context_date_max]        // get the context min dat
var overridden_dates_tbl =  CALCULATETABLE(ssr , cal_end_dates[Date] >=  date(1900,1,1) &&  cal_end_dates[Date] < date(2100,1,1)) -- get current filter context except all dates
// get the tables - break out of filter context (AKK) and override based on first purch and churn

var starting_custs =  Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_start && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks]  >= period_start)  // client before start of period,  churn after period started

var retained_custs = Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_start && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks]  >= period_end)  // client before start of period,  churn after period end

var churned_custs = Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks] >= period_start && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks] <= period_end)  // churned after period started, before period ended

var ending_custs =  Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_end && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks]  >= period_end)  // // client before end of period, churn after  period ended
// get the values based on temp tables
var starting_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,starting_custs) // look at last years rev for these

var retained_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,EXCEPT(starting_custs, churned_custs)) // look at last years rev for these
var new_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]), EXCEPT(ending_custs,starting_custs ) ) // not sure why we cannot use new customers here
var churned_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,EXCEPT(starting_custs,retained_custs)) * -1
var ending_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= period_end ,ending_custs)
return IF(isblank(res), 0, res)",Count of ssr history rev churned count. Respects the current filter context.,"#,0",8c2cefc7-1bd8-4631-83ec-b79c0a044a9c

powerbi\src\Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel\definition\tables\ssr_history.tmdl,Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel,ssr_history,meas.ssr_history_rev_ending_amt,"// get the period dates based on current filter contetxt

column4: var overridden_dates_tbl =  CALCULATETABLE(ssr , cal_end_dates[Date] >=  date(1900,1,1) &&  cal_end_dates[Date] < date(2100,1,1)) -- get current filter context except all dates
// get the tables - break out of filter context (AKK) and override based on first purch and churn

var starting_custs =  Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_start && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks]  >= period_start)  // client before start of period,  churn after period started

var retained_custs = Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_start && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks]  >= period_end)  // client before start of period,  churn after period end

var churned_custs = Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks] >= period_start && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks] <= period_end)  // churned after period started, before period ended

var ending_custs =  Filter((overridden_dates_tbl), ssr[trueai_first_purchase] <= period_end && ssr[col.trueai_churn_date_no_blanks]  >= period_end)  // // client before end of period, churn after  period ended
// get the values based on temp tables
var starting_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,starting_custs) // look at last years rev for these

var retained_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,EXCEPT(starting_custs, churned_custs)) // look at last years rev for these
var new_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]), EXCEPT(ending_custs,starting_custs ) ) // not sure why we cannot use new customers here
var churned_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= prev_period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= prev_period_end ,EXCEPT(starting_custs,retained_custs)) * -1
var ending_amt = CALCULATE(SUM(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]),  cal_end_dates[date] >= period_start &&  cal_end_dates[date] <= period_end ,ending_custs)
return IF(isblank(res), 0, res)",Measure calculating ssr history rev ending amt. Respects the current filter context.,"$ #,##0",93df14ad-ecb3-4bf0-8baa-da85c750bfba

column1: powerbi\src\Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel\definition\tables\ssr_history.tmdl,Dataset - Azure Data Lake - Sales Performance.SemanticModel,ssr_history,meas.ssr_history_rev_pareto_count,"var period_start = calculate(MIN(cal_end_dates[Date]))

column4: var  filt = CALCULATETABLE(SUMMARIZE(Filter(ALLSELECTED(ssr_history),ssr_history[opp_won_amt] <> 0 && RELATED(cal_end_dates[Date]) >= period_start &&  (RELATED(cal_end_dates[Date]) <= period_end )), ssr_history[_sys_ssr_id], ""acct_won_amount"", sum(ssr_history[opp_won_amt]))) // group by account
var filt_ranked = ADDCOLUMNS(filt, ""acct_won_rank"",  RANKX(filt, [acct_won_amount]))    -- rank by amount
var filt_ranked_totaled = ADDCOLUMNS(filt_ranked, ""acct_won_run_tot"",  SUMX(FIlter(filt_ranked, [acct_won_rank] >= EARLIER([acct_won_rank])), [acct_won_amount]) ) -- running total sorted by rank
var tot_amt = SUMX(filt, [acct_won_amount]) // get the total amount for all
var tot_count = COUNTX(filt,[acct_won_amount])  // get the total count for all
var pareto = tot_amt * .2  // calculate the top pareto amount inverted
var count_to_pareto = COUNTX(FILTER(filt_ranked_totaled, [acct_won_run_tot] >= pareto ), [acct_won_amount]) // apply a filter to the count where the running total is still less than bottom pareto
var res  = count_to_pareto // get the inverse of that count
return res// return count needed to get to 80%))))",Count of ssr history rev pareto count. Respects the current filter context.,"#,0",644b1d6c-2bbc-4511-9b05-286cf268c3b2
